        <p class="testo-name">Irfan Mustafa</p>
        <p class="testo-designation">CEO - Taskeen Health Initiative</p>
        <p class="testo-desc my-3">
          <svg width="10px" class="svg-inline--fa fa-quote-left fa-w-16 fa-2x" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" data-prefix="fas" data-icon="quote-left" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 512 512"><path fill="currentColor" d="M464 256h-80v-64c0-35.3 28.7-64 64-64h8c13.3 0 24-10.7 24-24V56c0-13.3-10.7-24-24-24h-8c-88.4 0-160 71.6-160 160v240c0 26.5 21.5 48 48 48h128c26.5 0 48-21.5 48-48V304c0-26.5-21.5-48-48-48zm-288 0H96v-64c0-35.3 28.7-64 64-64h8c13.3 0 24-10.7 24-24V56c0-13.3-10.7-24-24-24h-8C71.6 32 0 103.6 0 192v240c0 26.5 21.5 48 48 48h128c26.5 0 48-21.5 48-48V304c0-26.5-21.5-48-48-48z" class=""></path></svg>
          Taskeen is a non-profit that works for the promotion of well being and prevention of mental illness in Pakistan. We aim to change people’s attitudes and behaviors towards mental health and wellbeing through awareness, education, expression, and advocacy thereby achieving the goal of establishing the importance of mental health at par with physical health among the key stakeholders in of over 200 million. According to one estimate, around 50 million people in Pakistan suffer from mental disorders ranging from depression, substance and alcohol misuse, schizophrenia, bipolar disorder, and post-traumatic stress disorder most of whom are women. Unfortunately, there are very few mental health professionals in the country most of whom operate in major cities only, leaving the majority of sufferers at the mercy of informal mental health services including religious and faith healers. Like many societies around the world the psychological health care system is woefully deficient in Pakistan, and the way it is mainly managed explains why accessing psychological help is a taboo subject thereby preventing sufferers from seeking professional help. Taskeen worked with Digital Landscape to try and resolve some of the issues related to the access of professional counselling by way of an Artificial Intelligence driven mental health service which will be accessible via web based and mobile platforms. The AI based chat-bot has been successfully deployed, with the service available in both English as well as Urdu 24/7 throughout the country. We are confident that once access to AI driven mental health services is widely available, it can create a seismic change in the way mental health is perceived and managed, thereby preventing critical issues such as depression and suicidal thoughts. It is worth mentioning that according to one estimate, nearly 90 percent of the people who have died by suicide suffered from mental disorders. Digital Landscape is supporting us in developing this unique platform using AI. They offer top-notch quality and service with efficiency. We are pleased with their work across the board and would highly recommend their services.
